=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_GlitchHPF_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A neutral pure_tone sound, with saw_like oscillator character around 54 Hz, featuring punchy attack and compressed envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally rich.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: neutral
  crest_factor_db: compressed
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: rich
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 53.5887
  harmonic_decay_rate: -0.8376
  harmonic_regularity: 0.8291
  pitch_clarity: 9.9527
  inharmonicity: 0.0000
  type: saw_like
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -2.5060
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: GlitchHPF Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/GlitchHPF.html
// Tags: GlitchHPF, Classes, filter
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
//code that utilizes the glitch.
//warning!  extremely loud.
//note: might not sound the same on all soundcards
(
{GlitchHPF.ar(
    BrownNoise.ar(1.dup),
    0.5,
    Saw.kr(1, 10)
)}.play;
)
